WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.575 --> 00:00:08.576
Who are you?

2
00:00:08.609 --> 00:00:09.577
I'm her dad.

3
00:00:09.610 --> 00:00:11.245
Peyton: he loves his job.

4
00:00:11.279 --> 00:00:14.348
It's just not fair to ask him
to give that up.

5
00:00:14.382 --> 00:00:15.816
But I miss him
when he's away.

6
00:00:15.849 --> 00:00:17.651
You were right. Dan.

7
00:00:17.685 --> 00:00:20.254
We don't need a shrink to
identify this family's problem.

8
00:00:20.288 --> 00:00:21.489
You just made it obvious.

9
00:00:21.522 --> 00:00:23.157
I'm not his
only parent. Deb.

10
00:00:23.191 --> 00:00:25.126
Why don't you ride
with the old man. Nathan?

11
00:00:25.159 --> 00:00:26.727
Come on. Nathan.

12
00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:28.696
Let the kid make up his own
mind. What do you say. son?

13
00:00:30.631 --> 00:00:32.600
I need to connect more
with Lucas.

14
00:00:32.633 --> 00:00:34.568
I thought you guys were
already doing that.

15
00:00:34.602 --> 00:00:37.438
The making out thing is great.
but it only goes so far.

16
00:00:37.471 --> 00:00:38.706
Dan: where do you get off

17
00:00:38.739 --> 00:00:40.574
telling Nathan
he can quit the team?

18
00:00:40.608 --> 00:00:42.276
I didn't tell him
he could quit.

19
00:00:42.310 --> 00:00:43.777
He wanted to talk.
We talked.

20
00:00:43.811 --> 00:00:46.280
I don't mind you playing
daddy to one of my offspring.

21
00:00:46.314 --> 00:00:48.216
but leave the good one
alone.

22
00:00:48.249 --> 00:00:52.120
You're the first really great
guy that I've ever dated.

23
00:00:52.153 --> 00:00:53.754
And that really scares me

24
00:00:53.787 --> 00:00:56.757
because I never
gave a rat's ass before.

25
00:00:56.790 --> 00:01:00.161
I give a rat's ass
about you. too.

26
00:01:04.598 --> 00:01:07.401
I'm done. I just thought you
should be the first to know.

27
00:01:07.435 --> 00:01:08.569
Me?

28
00:01:08.602 --> 00:01:11.739
Yeah. you wanted
my world. man.

29
00:01:13.474 --> 00:01:14.642
It's all yours.

30
00:01:18.812 --> 00:01:21.615
* I don't want to be anything

31
00:01:21.649 --> 00:01:25.319
* other than what I've been
trying to be lately *

32
00:01:25.353 --> 00:01:27.721
* all I have to do
is think of me *

33
00:01:27.755 --> 00:01:31.625
* and I have peace of mind

34
00:01:31.659 --> 00:01:33.594
* I don't want to be anything

35
00:01:33.627 --> 00:01:37.698
* other than what I've been
trying to be lately *

36
00:01:37.731 --> 00:01:40.268
* all I have to do
is think of me *

37
00:01:40.301 --> 00:01:43.471
* and I have peace of mind

38
00:01:43.504 --> 00:01:45.673
* I'm tired of looking 'round

39
00:01:45.706 --> 00:01:47.575
* wondering what I gotta do

40
00:01:47.608 --> 00:01:50.244
* or who I'm supposed to be

41
00:01:50.278 --> 00:01:52.480
* I don't want to be anything

42
00:01:52.513 --> 00:01:56.484
* other than me

43
00:01:58.219 --> 00:01:59.687
hey. honey.
Hey. dad.

44
00:01:59.720 --> 00:02:01.222
[ Grunts ]

45
00:02:01.255 --> 00:02:03.524
What's going on
with the unabomber look?

46
00:02:03.557 --> 00:02:05.559
I was going
for George Clooney.

47
00:02:05.593 --> 00:02:06.694
Go further.

48
00:02:06.727 --> 00:02:08.296
Ouch.
that's right. though.

49
00:02:08.329 --> 00:02:10.464
You're not used to seeing me
like this.

50
00:02:10.498 --> 00:02:12.733
See. when I'm on the job.
i usually let it grow.

51
00:02:12.766 --> 00:02:14.602
Then I shave it off
right before I come home.

52
00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:16.337
Kind of a ritual.

53
00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:19.373
Well. just make sure you find
your razor day after tomorrow.

54
00:02:19.407 --> 00:02:21.575
And after that. I'm gonna be
shaving a lot more often.

55
00:02:21.609 --> 00:02:22.610
Okay.

56
00:02:22.643 --> 00:02:24.478
Hey. Brooke.
hey. rake boy.

57
00:02:24.512 --> 00:02:26.647
I see nobody uses
the doorbell still.

58
00:02:26.680 --> 00:02:29.617
Papa Peyton. the scruffy
thing's working for you.

59
00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:31.785
What are you guys up
to so early?

60
00:02:31.819 --> 00:02:33.587
I don't know.
Peyton just asked --

61
00:02:33.621 --> 00:02:35.689
you know what? You'll find out
when you get home.

62
00:02:35.723 --> 00:02:37.325
Not even a little hint?

63
00:02:37.358 --> 00:02:39.360
Mnh-mnh. not even.
I love you.

64
00:02:39.393 --> 00:02:41.662
You better.
I love you. too. honey.

65
00:02:41.695 --> 00:02:42.663
Bye.

66
00:02:44.365 --> 00:02:46.234
So. what's the surprise?

67
00:02:46.267 --> 00:02:48.736
I need your help
with something.

68
00:02:48.769 --> 00:02:49.703
Come on.

69
00:02:53.241 --> 00:02:54.742
[ Whistles ]

70
00:02:54.775 --> 00:02:55.776
Damn. that's nice.

71
00:02:55.809 --> 00:02:57.578
This your dad's?

72
00:02:57.611 --> 00:03:00.314
Yeah. he hasn't driven it
in. like. a year. though.

73
00:03:00.348 --> 00:03:01.982
Do you think
you can get it to run?

74
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.517
Of course he can.

75
00:03:03.551 --> 00:03:05.853
And he's gonna look good
doing it. too.

76
00:03:05.886 --> 00:03:08.956
in a tight little wife beater.
maybe some grease smudges.

77
00:03:08.989 --> 00:03:12.260
I was thinking maybe you could
help me wash and wax it.

78
00:03:12.293 --> 00:03:13.561
I'm glad to help.

79
00:03:13.594 --> 00:03:16.564
I just want to do something
nice for him.

80
00:03:16.597 --> 00:03:18.466
since he's coming home.

81
00:03:18.499 --> 00:03:19.933
All right.

82
00:03:19.967 --> 00:03:22.836
I'll go get my tools.

83
00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:26.607
[ Doorbell rings ]

84
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.841
Surprise!

85
00:03:27.875 --> 00:03:29.710
You answer the door
in your underwear?

86
00:03:29.743 --> 00:03:32.480
Grandma. grandpa.
what are you guys doing here?

87
00:03:32.513 --> 00:03:36.317
Royal. may. oh. um.
what a surprise.

88
00:03:36.350 --> 00:03:37.918
Well. thanks
for the warm welcome.

89
00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:39.920
I told you this ambush
was a bad idea.

90
00:03:39.953 --> 00:03:41.722
He's dragging me
to another one --

91
00:03:41.755 --> 00:03:43.591
nobody's dragging anybody
anywhere.

92
00:03:43.624 --> 00:03:46.494
I told him that the only
way I'd go

93
00:03:46.527 --> 00:03:48.629
is if we came by here
for Danny's birthday.

94
00:03:48.662 --> 00:03:51.299
Oh. Dan's birthday.
of course.

95
00:03:51.332 --> 00:03:53.334
[ Chuckles ] yeah.

96
00:03:53.367 --> 00:03:55.669
Well. you gonna leave us
standing out here all morning

97
00:03:55.703 --> 00:03:57.438
freezing our asses off?

98
00:03:57.471 --> 00:03:58.306
Come on in.

99
00:03:58.339 --> 00:03:59.940
Come on. Kiss gran.

100
00:03:59.973 --> 00:04:03.644
Looks like you put on a few
there. Deb. Looks good on you.

101
00:04:06.046 --> 00:04:07.415
Dan...

102
00:04:07.448 --> 00:04:09.850
You remembered.
I'm touched.

103
00:04:09.883 --> 00:04:13.721
I'm not here to wish you
a happy birthday.

104
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:15.589
but your parents are.

105
00:04:15.623 --> 00:04:16.657
What?

106
00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:17.958
They showed up at the house.

107
00:04:17.991 --> 00:04:19.760
Apparently.
you never told them

108
00:04:19.793 --> 00:04:21.495
that you're not living there.

109
00:04:21.529 --> 00:04:23.664
[ Sighs ]
how'd they take it?

110
00:04:23.697 --> 00:04:25.032
You think I told them?

111
00:04:25.065 --> 00:04:28.369
I'm not gonna be on the
receiving end of that.

112
00:04:28.402 --> 00:04:29.537
That's your job.

113
00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:30.871
How long are they here?

114
00:04:30.904 --> 00:04:33.341
Just tonight.
but it gets better.

115
00:04:33.374 --> 00:04:36.310
Your mother is cooking you
a big birthday dinner.

116
00:04:36.344 --> 00:04:37.578
Oh. perfect.

117
00:04:37.611 --> 00:04:39.613
All right. so what are we
gonna do?

118
00:04:39.647 --> 00:04:41.582
We are not going to do
anything.

119
00:04:41.615 --> 00:04:44.418
You are going to go
to the house right now

120
00:04:44.452 --> 00:04:46.420
and tell them
we're separated.

121
00:04:46.454 --> 00:04:48.489
No. we're doing
the counseling.

122
00:04:48.522 --> 00:04:50.758
We're gonna work this
thing out. right?

123
00:04:50.791 --> 00:04:51.692
Isn't that the whole point?

124
00:04:51.725 --> 00:04:52.960
It is.

125
00:04:52.993 --> 00:04:54.662
Do you really want them
weighing in

126
00:04:54.695 --> 00:04:55.996
on the state of our marriage?

127
00:04:56.029 --> 00:04:57.631
Do you remember
when we told them

128
00:04:57.665 --> 00:04:59.600
we weren't gonna have
any more kids?

129
00:04:59.633 --> 00:05:01.469
How many times
did my dad call you?

130
00:05:01.502 --> 00:05:04.104
Now you don't even have the
option of hanging up on them.

131
00:05:04.137 --> 00:05:05.706
Go on. Dan.
Just say it.

132
00:05:05.739 --> 00:05:07.475
We go through the motions
tonight.

133
00:05:07.508 --> 00:05:09.710
Get it over with.
send them on their way.

134
00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:11.044
Go back to working
on us.

135
00:05:11.078 --> 00:05:13.414
Besides.
it might do some good

136
00:05:13.447 --> 00:05:16.884
to try and remember what it's
like to be a normal family.

137
00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:21.922
Fine. just for tonight.

138
00:05:21.955 --> 00:05:24.091
Just for tonight.

139
00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:31.665
[ Sighs ]

140
00:05:34.067 --> 00:05:35.669
Good morning. sir.

141
00:05:35.703 --> 00:05:36.870
Table or counter?

142
00:05:36.904 --> 00:05:39.673
Actually. I'm looking
for Karen.

143
00:05:39.707 --> 00:05:42.776
She's in Italy right now --
cooking school.

144
00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:44.712
Good for her.
[ Chuckles ]

145
00:05:44.745 --> 00:05:46.747
How's that boy of hers
doing?

146
00:05:46.780 --> 00:05:48.081
Uh. Lucas is great.

147
00:05:48.115 --> 00:05:50.684
She calls in every once
in a while.

148
00:05:50.718 --> 00:05:52.853
Do you want me to leave
a message?

149
00:05:52.886 --> 00:05:54.622
No. that's all right.

150
00:05:54.655 --> 00:05:58.426
I'll just catch her the next
time I'm passing through.

151
00:05:58.459 --> 00:06:01.529
Okay. can I tell her
who stopped by. Mr...

152
00:06:01.562 --> 00:06:02.796
Just an old friend.

153
00:06:16.577 --> 00:06:20.648
Well. it's not the battery.
It's probably the starter.

154
00:06:20.681 --> 00:06:22.650
You can fix that. right?

155
00:06:22.683 --> 00:06:26.086
[ Chuckles ] yeah. it
shouldn't be a problem.

156
00:06:26.119 --> 00:06:27.821
[ Inhales deeply ]

157
00:06:27.855 --> 00:06:29.990
Oh. it's an amazing car.

158
00:06:30.023 --> 00:06:32.192
Mm. it's an amazing guy.

159
00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:33.994
Oh. mm.

160
00:06:35.596 --> 00:06:37.865
Is that what you got me
this thing for?

161
00:06:37.898 --> 00:06:39.032
Uh-huh.

162
00:06:43.003 --> 00:06:46.039
I was just getting
started.

163
00:06:46.073 --> 00:06:47.808
Sadly. so was I.

164
00:06:47.841 --> 00:06:49.543
What's wrong?

165
00:06:49.577 --> 00:06:52.646
I'm just worried
about my dad.

166
00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.982
All right.
i just checked online.

167
00:06:55.015 --> 00:06:58.486
and now they're saying
it's a category 3 hurricane.

168
00:06:58.519 --> 00:07:00.688
All right. and you already
checked the webcam. right?

169
00:07:00.721 --> 00:07:01.555
Yeah. it's out.

170
00:07:01.589 --> 00:07:06.760
Maybe he turned it off.

171
00:07:06.794 --> 00:07:09.162
Anyway. aren't
dredging boats huge?

172
00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:11.499
He wouldn't be
on the dredging boat.

173
00:07:11.532 --> 00:07:14.502
He'd be on this little. tiny
transport headed back to shore.

174
00:07:14.535 --> 00:07:16.003
and that's what worries me.

175
00:07:16.036 --> 00:07:18.606
Okay. Peyton. just stop.
Don't do this to yourself.

176
00:07:18.639 --> 00:07:19.873
All right?

177
00:07:19.907 --> 00:07:21.575
Just because
he hasn't checked in

178
00:07:21.609 --> 00:07:23.544
doesn't mean something's
happened.

179
00:07:23.577 --> 00:07:25.579
It doesn't mean it hasn't.
either.

180
00:07:31.084 --> 00:07:36.056
So. this. um. dinner thing is
gonna be pretty bad. huh?

181
00:07:36.089 --> 00:07:37.157
Massacre.

182
00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:38.959
My grandma's okay.

183
00:07:38.992 --> 00:07:42.730
It's just my gramp
is pretty intense.

184
00:07:42.763 --> 00:07:44.532
You've met my dad.

185
00:07:44.565 --> 00:07:46.767
Just imagine
where he comes from.

186
00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:47.801
Scary.

187
00:07:47.835 --> 00:07:50.070
Yeah.
you should come tonight.

188
00:07:50.103 --> 00:07:52.272
Maybe it'll make everybody
behave.

189
00:07:52.305 --> 00:07:53.674
[ Laughs ]

190
00:07:53.707 --> 00:07:55.576
I'll come
if you want me to.

191
00:07:55.609 --> 00:07:56.810
No. I wasn't serious.

192
00:07:56.844 --> 00:07:59.112
I wouldn't put you
through that.

193
00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:03.684
I mean. if you're asking.
of course. my answer's yes.

194
00:08:03.717 --> 00:08:05.653
Well. then. I'm asking.

195
00:08:05.686 --> 00:08:07.555
Well. then. I'm coming.

196
00:08:08.889 --> 00:08:11.959
Charcoal finish.
custom-leather package.

197
00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:14.962
What you want
is a champagne interior.

198
00:08:14.995 --> 00:08:16.564
I'm here to see
the manager.

199
00:08:16.597 --> 00:08:17.731
Excuse me.

200
00:08:17.765 --> 00:08:19.232
Hey. fella.
you ought to know

201
00:08:19.266 --> 00:08:21.001
who you're doing
business with.

202
00:08:21.034 --> 00:08:22.770
Is there a problem?

203
00:08:22.803 --> 00:08:25.272
Well. you're buying from
Dan Scott. basketball legend.

204
00:08:25.305 --> 00:08:28.208
Still holds the all-time
scoring record for Tree Hill.

205
00:08:28.241 --> 00:08:30.077
Made all-state
his senior year.

206
00:08:30.110 --> 00:08:31.078
No kidding?

207
00:08:31.111 --> 00:08:32.212
My dad.

208
00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:34.081
I figured.
You play college. too?

209
00:08:34.114 --> 00:08:37.084
Would've. but he blew his
knee out in his freshman year.

210
00:08:37.117 --> 00:08:38.251
He got robbed.

211
00:08:38.285 --> 00:08:39.987
Would have been one
of the greats.

212
00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:41.889
Dad. Mr. Miller's really not
interested.

213
00:08:41.922 --> 00:08:43.924
I tell you what.
meet me in my office. okay?

214
00:08:43.957 --> 00:08:45.793
I'll be right in.
Champagne interior. right?

215
00:08:45.826 --> 00:08:47.094
All right.

216
00:08:47.127 --> 00:08:48.662
What? somebody's got to brag
on you.

217
00:08:48.696 --> 00:08:50.664
And you're not gonna close
that sale

218
00:08:50.698 --> 00:08:53.701
without your old man's help.
You know that. don't you?

219
00:08:53.734 --> 00:08:56.203
You always were
my biggest promoter.

220
00:08:56.236 --> 00:08:57.838
[ Chuckles ]
yeah.

221
00:08:57.871 --> 00:09:00.608
Hey. still in shape.
Good for you.

222
00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:05.879
Well. you're home.

223
00:09:05.913 --> 00:09:07.715
Listen. I called Nathan.

224
00:09:07.748 --> 00:09:10.684
I told him not to tell dad
he's not going to practice.

225
00:09:10.718 --> 00:09:12.119
You mean
that he quit the team?

226
00:09:12.152 --> 00:09:13.654
You know what I mean.

227
00:09:13.687 --> 00:09:16.056
I also told Keith
to avoid the subject.

228
00:09:16.089 --> 00:09:18.792
Any other lies I should
remember to tell?

229
00:09:18.826 --> 00:09:21.762
I'm trying to protect our son
from my father. okay?

230
00:09:21.795 --> 00:09:24.064
You don't even see
the irony. do you?

231
00:09:24.097 --> 00:09:26.099
Mom. you look beautiful
as ever.

232
00:09:26.133 --> 00:09:27.735
God bless you for a liar.

233
00:09:27.768 --> 00:09:29.670
I compliment you.
you call me a liar.

234
00:09:29.703 --> 00:09:31.304
You look tired.

235
00:09:31.338 --> 00:09:34.241
Hey. son. what's the deal?
No more Charlotte hornets?

236
00:09:34.274 --> 00:09:35.876
New Orleans can have 'em.

237
00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:38.812
I don't think they
have the playoffs --

238
00:09:38.846 --> 00:09:40.313
no sports talk.

239
00:09:40.347 --> 00:09:41.915
[ Doorbell rings ]
oh. come on.

240
00:09:41.949 --> 00:09:43.617
[ Clears throat ]

241
00:09:43.651 --> 00:09:45.919
Oh. I just became head
of the table. didn't I?

242
00:09:45.953 --> 00:09:46.954
Mom.

243
00:09:46.987 --> 00:09:49.289
You look great.

244
00:09:49.322 --> 00:09:52.159
Well. look what the cat
dragged in.

245
00:09:52.192 --> 00:09:54.762
It's good to see you.
too. dad.

246
00:09:54.795 --> 00:09:55.763
Uh-huh.

247
00:09:55.796 --> 00:09:57.064
Happy birthday. Danny.

248
00:09:57.097 --> 00:09:58.699
Yeah. thanks.

249
00:09:58.732 --> 00:10:01.735
Come on. have a seat.
Dinner is almost ready.

250
00:10:01.769 --> 00:10:04.037
Danny. will you pour
some wine. please?

251
00:10:04.071 --> 00:10:04.805
I'm on it.

252
00:10:04.838 --> 00:10:06.273
Amen to that.

253
00:10:06.306 --> 00:10:09.677
Listen. mom. we're gonna
need another place setting.

254
00:10:09.710 --> 00:10:10.778
I invited a guest.

255
00:10:10.811 --> 00:10:13.714
A date?
Oh. my goodness.

256
00:10:13.747 --> 00:10:17.417
Grandpa. grandma.
this is Haley.

257
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:20.053
Oh. Haley.
nice to meet you.

258
00:10:20.087 --> 00:10:21.955
Nice to meet you. too.

259
00:10:26.794 --> 00:10:29.096
Nathan. you're looking more
and more like your old man

260
00:10:29.129 --> 00:10:30.898
every day.

261
00:10:30.931 --> 00:10:33.233
We all know where he gets
his good looks. don't we?

262
00:10:33.266 --> 00:10:34.968
You sit right here
next to me. honey.

263
00:10:35.002 --> 00:10:37.805
[ Doorbell rings ]
may: I'll get it.

264
00:10:37.838 --> 00:10:40.373
Haley: everything
looks so nice.

265
00:10:40.407 --> 00:10:42.442
Oh. my goodness.
Whitey.

266
00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:44.244
Good evening. everybody.

267
00:10:44.277 --> 00:10:45.713
Sorry I'm late.

268
00:10:45.746 --> 00:10:47.347
Glad you came?

269
00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:48.749
Yeah.

270
00:10:51.118 --> 00:10:53.020
[ Breathing heavily ]

271
00:10:53.053 --> 00:10:55.188
All right. try it again.

272
00:10:55.222 --> 00:10:57.758
[ Engine turns over ]

273
00:10:57.791 --> 00:10:58.726
We got power.

274
00:10:58.759 --> 00:10:59.727
Whoo!

275
00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:01.929
Peyton. come check it out.

276
00:11:05.498 --> 00:11:07.200
What is it?

277
00:11:07.234 --> 00:11:09.803
I just got a phone call.

278
00:11:09.837 --> 00:11:11.204
Um. the storm.

279
00:11:11.238 --> 00:11:14.474
My dad's transport
is missing.

280
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:17.210
There were three guys on it.

281
00:11:17.244 --> 00:11:19.713
They recovered a body.

282
00:11:19.747 --> 00:11:22.049
What did they tell you?

283
00:11:22.082 --> 00:11:25.452
I have to go see
if it's him.

284
00:11:36.163 --> 00:11:37.865
No. she'd freak out.
I'd rather not upset her.

285
00:11:37.898 --> 00:11:39.032
Besides. it's not
gonna be my dad.

286
00:11:39.066 --> 00:11:40.400
Of course it's not.

287
00:11:40.433 --> 00:11:42.202
Let's go ahead
and get this over with.

288
00:11:42.235 --> 00:11:43.904
We have a 4-hour drive
ahead of us.

289
00:11:43.937 --> 00:11:45.739
A 4-hour drive
into a storm?

290
00:11:45.773 --> 00:11:47.140
The storm's passing through.

291
00:11:47.174 --> 00:11:49.843
By the time we get there.
it should be gone.

292
00:11:49.877 --> 00:11:51.178
Okay. wait a second.

293
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:53.513
Shouldn't somebody stay here
by the phone

294
00:11:53.546 --> 00:11:55.082
in case your dad calls?

295
00:11:55.115 --> 00:11:56.349
I will.
You go with Peyton.

296
00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:58.151
You sure?

297
00:11:58.185 --> 00:12:00.921
You're good in a crisis.
not that there's gonna be one.

298
00:12:00.954 --> 00:12:03.090
But I would end up
falling apart.

299
00:12:03.123 --> 00:12:05.158
and you'd end up
taking care of me.

300
00:12:05.192 --> 00:12:06.794
which is not the point.

301
00:12:06.827 --> 00:12:09.997
So...i love you.

302
00:12:10.030 --> 00:12:13.466
It's gonna be okay.

303
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:15.202
You're the best.

304
00:12:18.806 --> 00:12:23.043
I'll call you guys
if I hear anything.

305
00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:25.112
Royal: how's the team doing
this year. whitey?

306
00:12:25.145 --> 00:12:27.080
Oh. we're --
still undefeated. actually.

307
00:12:28.982 --> 00:12:32.319
Dad. you still rooting
for the magic these days?

308
00:12:32.352 --> 00:12:36.223
Please. no talk of sports
until after dinner. okay?

309
00:12:36.256 --> 00:12:39.827
Good idea. mom.
I'm sorry.

310
00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:42.395
Well. Nathan. what are you
averaging these days?

311
00:12:42.429 --> 00:12:44.832
You know. your dad
had 27 1/2 a game.

312
00:12:44.865 --> 00:12:45.833
You beat that yet?

313
00:12:45.866 --> 00:12:47.134
Royal. we just --

314
00:12:47.167 --> 00:12:49.169
I'm asking the boy
a question. may.

315
00:12:49.202 --> 00:12:50.237
[ Sighs ]

316
00:12:52.072 --> 00:12:54.441
Uh. maybe you should ask
the old man.

317
00:12:59.079 --> 00:13:01.915
Uh. 24 points a game.
i think. isn't it?

318
00:13:01.949 --> 00:13:03.116
So. 24 a game. huh?

319
00:13:03.150 --> 00:13:04.818
You're gonna have to get that up

320
00:13:04.852 --> 00:13:06.119
if you're gonna beat
the old man.

321
00:13:06.153 --> 00:13:07.520
Yeah. your dad's star

322
00:13:07.554 --> 00:13:09.589
would have risen through
the roof at Carolina

323
00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:11.925
if it hadn't been
for that damn knee of his.

324
00:13:11.959 --> 00:13:12.893
How are your knees?

325
00:13:12.926 --> 00:13:14.161
No worries.

326
00:13:14.194 --> 00:13:16.263
He's got great knees.

327
00:13:16.296 --> 00:13:19.132
[ Laughter ]

328
00:13:19.166 --> 00:13:20.567
Uh-huh.

329
00:13:20.600 --> 00:13:23.536
Of course. now. Danny takes
after his old man.

330
00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:25.873
never let adversity stop him.

331
00:13:25.906 --> 00:13:29.576
Too bad Keith takes after his
mother's side of the family.

332
00:13:29.609 --> 00:13:31.111
Lucky for him.

333
00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:34.581
I'd drink to that.
but I got to get a refill.

334
00:13:34.614 --> 00:13:36.016
Yeah.

335
00:13:36.049 --> 00:13:38.151
Well. I should see
about the cake.

336
00:13:38.185 --> 00:13:40.220
Mm. I'll go do that.
Mrs. Scott.

337
00:13:40.253 --> 00:13:41.488
Want to come help?

338
00:13:41.521 --> 00:13:43.423
Yeah. yeah.
the cake. right.

339
00:13:48.328 --> 00:13:51.198
I warned you
it was gonna be intense.

340
00:13:51.231 --> 00:13:53.266
Ohh. insane
is more like it.

341
00:13:53.300 --> 00:13:56.169
You know.
there's a door right there.

342
00:13:56.203 --> 00:13:58.238
We could sneak out.
Nobody'd even notice.

343
00:13:58.271 --> 00:13:59.973
Tempting.

344
00:14:00.007 --> 00:14:04.277
Um. so. how often do your
grandparents come to town?

345
00:14:04.311 --> 00:14:07.080
A couple times a year.
Why?

346
00:14:09.082 --> 00:14:11.484
Haley. you've got that look.

347
00:14:11.518 --> 00:14:13.086
What look?

348
00:14:13.120 --> 00:14:14.421
The look you get when you
want to tell me something.

349
00:14:14.454 --> 00:14:16.223
but you don't really
want to tell me.

350
00:14:16.256 --> 00:14:18.025
No. I don't. and you shouldn't
know that look yet.

351
00:14:18.058 --> 00:14:19.359
What is it?

352
00:14:19.392 --> 00:14:22.462
Your grandfather came
by the café today.

353
00:14:22.495 --> 00:14:24.197
and he asked for Karen.

354
00:14:24.231 --> 00:14:25.933
He did?

355
00:14:25.966 --> 00:14:27.300
I just got the feeling

356
00:14:27.334 --> 00:14:30.203
like they've been keeping
in touch.

357
00:14:30.237 --> 00:14:31.271
Does Lucas know him?

358
00:14:31.304 --> 00:14:33.040
No. they've never even met.

359
00:14:33.073 --> 00:14:35.108
but your grandfather
asked about him.

360
00:14:35.142 --> 00:14:36.944
That doesn't make any sense.

361
00:14:36.977 --> 00:14:39.546
My grandpa acts like my dad's
the second coming.

362
00:14:39.579 --> 00:14:41.248
Why would he visit Karen?

363
00:14:41.281 --> 00:14:43.683
I don't know.
I don't want to start anything.

364
00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:45.152
I'm just telling you.

365
00:14:45.185 --> 00:14:47.354
You know what?
My family's so screwed up.

366
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:50.190
nothing new would make
a difference right now.

367
00:14:50.223 --> 00:14:51.191
Don't worry about it.

368
00:14:58.999 --> 00:14:59.532
You warm enough?

369
00:14:59.566 --> 00:15:01.134
I'm okay.

370
00:15:01.168 --> 00:15:03.703
I should probably get the
heater fixed in here. huh?

371
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:05.305
[ Laughs ]

372
00:15:05.338 --> 00:15:07.107
I could have Keith
take a look at it for you.

373
00:15:07.140 --> 00:15:08.608
He's really good
at that stuff.

374
00:15:10.610 --> 00:15:14.214
You want me to stop
and get some coffees?

375
00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.182
I'm fine.

376
00:15:21.321 --> 00:15:24.091
Thanks for doing this
for me. Luke.

377
00:15:24.124 --> 00:15:26.493
That's what friends
are for. right?

378
00:15:26.526 --> 00:15:29.062
Yeah.

379
00:15:37.337 --> 00:15:39.139
Now what?

380
00:15:45.312 --> 00:15:46.646
What's going on?

381
00:15:46.679 --> 00:15:49.049
The bridge is up
'cause of the storm.

382
00:15:49.082 --> 00:15:50.617
It'll be open
in the morning.

383
00:15:50.650 --> 00:15:52.052
We have an emergency.

384
00:15:52.085 --> 00:15:53.386
We have to get across
the bridge.

385
00:15:53.420 --> 00:15:55.588
I'm sorry. miss.
but it's not safe.

386
00:15:55.622 --> 00:15:57.490
Is there another way
through?

387
00:15:57.524 --> 00:16:00.260
Only the ferries.
but the channel's too rough.

388
00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:01.361
so they're not running.

389
00:16:01.394 --> 00:16:03.163
What are we supposed to do?

390
00:16:03.196 --> 00:16:05.032
Hopefully we'll be able to lower
the bridge in the morning.

391
00:16:05.065 --> 00:16:06.366
6:00 A.M.

392
00:16:06.399 --> 00:16:08.301
There's a motel right
down the road.

393
00:16:08.335 --> 00:16:11.038
Might want to grab yourself
a room before they're all gone.

394
00:16:17.177 --> 00:16:18.711
[ Sighs ]

395
00:16:21.748 --> 00:16:23.683
[ Blowing ]

396
00:16:23.716 --> 00:16:25.118
There you go.

397
00:16:27.387 --> 00:16:29.522
So. Nate. how's your game
this year?

398
00:16:29.556 --> 00:16:30.523
May: here we go again.

399
00:16:30.557 --> 00:16:32.392
Just cover your ears. may.

400
00:16:32.425 --> 00:16:35.495
I just want to know how my
grandson's doing on the team.

401
00:16:35.528 --> 00:16:37.164
I already told you. dad.

402
00:16:37.197 --> 00:16:39.432
No. you didn't.
You didn't tell me Jack.

403
00:16:39.466 --> 00:16:42.535
Every time I mention it.
you change the damn subject.

404
00:16:42.569 --> 00:16:46.239
Will somebody around here
tell me what's going on?

405
00:16:46.273 --> 00:16:51.244
Nathan? whitey? Anybody?

406
00:16:51.278 --> 00:16:54.114
Nathan. I think
you better take this one.

407
00:16:58.118 --> 00:16:59.686
I quit the team.
all right?

408
00:16:59.719 --> 00:17:02.689
You quit the -- what do you
mean you quit the team?

409
00:17:02.722 --> 00:17:06.159
He didn't quit the team.
He's just taking some time off.

410
00:17:06.193 --> 00:17:08.261
No. he's not.
Please stop lying. Dan.

411
00:17:08.295 --> 00:17:10.130
Were you ever gonna
tell me this?

412
00:17:10.163 --> 00:17:11.831
That's a hell of a thing
to keep to yourself.

413
00:17:11.864 --> 00:17:13.266
Yeah. you're one to talk.

414
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:14.767
What's that supposed
to mean?

415
00:17:14.801 --> 00:17:16.703
I know you visit Karen
at the café. all right?

416
00:17:16.736 --> 00:17:18.138
What's that about?

417
00:17:18.171 --> 00:17:20.307
That's none
of your damn business.

418
00:17:20.340 --> 00:17:22.542
I guess somebody's got
a big mouth.

419
00:17:22.575 --> 00:17:24.311
Will you shut up. grandpa?

420
00:17:24.344 --> 00:17:26.146
Don't you talk to me
like that!

421
00:17:26.179 --> 00:17:29.116
Back off. royal.
I've had enough of your crap.

422
00:17:29.149 --> 00:17:31.184
Nathan is not the problem.

423
00:17:31.218 --> 00:17:33.520
Would someone
please explain?

424
00:17:38.325 --> 00:17:41.594
Dan has been riding Nathan
for the past six years

425
00:17:41.628 --> 00:17:43.296
about that damn game.

426
00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:43.863
Deb. stop.

427
00:17:43.896 --> 00:17:45.498
Riding him so hard

428
00:17:45.532 --> 00:17:49.136
that Nathan took drugs
so he could measure up.

429
00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:52.239
until he had to be rushed
to the hospital.

430
00:17:52.272 --> 00:17:56.109
He could have died because
of this insane pressure

431
00:17:56.143 --> 00:17:58.178
to put a ball through a hoop.

432
00:17:58.211 --> 00:18:02.149
But none of that is my son's
fault. royal.

433
00:18:02.182 --> 00:18:03.550
It's your son's.

434
00:18:06.519 --> 00:18:10.290
Danny. you of all people --
how dare you.

435
00:18:10.323 --> 00:18:13.260
You know
how much you hated it

436
00:18:13.293 --> 00:18:17.230
when your daddy bullied you
to be better.

437
00:18:17.264 --> 00:18:19.132
I never bullied him!

438
00:18:19.166 --> 00:18:22.202
And when you wanted a way out.
i gave you one.

439
00:18:22.235 --> 00:18:25.672
All these years. I protected
you. I lied for you.

440
00:18:25.705 --> 00:18:29.276
And now you're doing
the same thing to your son?

441
00:18:29.309 --> 00:18:31.811
What lie?
What are you talking about?

442
00:18:31.844 --> 00:18:33.580
In college...

443
00:18:33.613 --> 00:18:38.251
His knee injury --
it wasn't permanent.

444
00:18:38.285 --> 00:18:42.155
Danny quit.
and I helped him.

445
00:18:52.565 --> 00:18:53.733
It's not like that. dad.

446
00:18:53.766 --> 00:18:55.168
Oh. stop it. Dan.

447
00:18:55.202 --> 00:18:56.936
It's time the truth
came out.

448
00:18:56.969 --> 00:19:00.473
Will somebody tell me what
in the hell is going on here?

449
00:19:00.507 --> 00:19:02.475
You were on the road
when Danny hurt his knee.

450
00:19:02.509 --> 00:19:03.943
so we lied.

451
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:07.780
You told me it was
a degenerative knee condition.

452
00:19:07.814 --> 00:19:11.451
You looked me in the eye.
and you told me that.

453
00:19:11.484 --> 00:19:13.353
Don't you see. royal?

454
00:19:13.386 --> 00:19:17.524
He was never gonna be the star
that you wanted him to be.

455
00:19:17.557 --> 00:19:19.626
You just couldn't see that.

456
00:19:19.659 --> 00:19:22.595
The boy had two choices --

457
00:19:22.629 --> 00:19:26.733
to fail in front of you
or to quit.

458
00:19:26.766 --> 00:19:29.302
Either way. he lost.

459
00:19:34.374 --> 00:19:35.775
So you just quit

460
00:19:35.808 --> 00:19:39.646
without even being man enough
to own up to it.

461
00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:43.416
There's more to the story. dad.
You don't know the whole story.

462
00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:45.818
Me too. Come on. Haley.
I'll take you home.

463
00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:47.820
Thanks for dinner.

464
00:19:47.854 --> 00:19:51.224
Well. I can show
myself out.

465
00:19:51.258 --> 00:19:53.293
Thank you. may.
Deb.

466
00:19:57.364 --> 00:19:59.766
Happy birthday. Danny.

467
00:20:01.634 --> 00:20:03.870
Danny. don't --

468
00:20:03.903 --> 00:20:04.837
why?

469
00:20:09.008 --> 00:20:10.777
[ Clears throat ]

470
00:20:10.810 --> 00:20:14.347
Well. I guess
I'll do the dishes.

471
00:20:23.790 --> 00:20:26.793
All right. let's just try
to get some sleep.

472
00:20:26.826 --> 00:20:30.430
Then we'll be at the bridge
as soon as it opens up.

473
00:20:30.463 --> 00:20:32.499
What did he say.
6:00 A.M.?

474
00:20:32.532 --> 00:20:33.900
We'll be there at 5:00.

475
00:20:33.933 --> 00:20:35.568
[ Laughing ]

476
00:20:37.003 --> 00:20:38.571
What?

477
00:20:38.605 --> 00:20:42.309
I'm in a hurry to find out
if my dad is dead.

478
00:20:42.342 --> 00:20:44.477
It's just kind of surreal.

479
00:20:49.081 --> 00:20:50.850
Yeah. it's pretty messed up.

480
00:20:50.883 --> 00:20:52.585
You know how in dreams

481
00:20:52.619 --> 00:20:56.389
you're always trying to get
to someplace you need to be.

482
00:20:56.423 --> 00:20:58.725
but you never really
get there?

483
00:20:58.758 --> 00:20:59.792
Yeah.

484
00:21:04.030 --> 00:21:06.633
I wish I could wake up.

485
00:21:09.569 --> 00:21:12.405
Maybe we should try
to get some sleep.

486
00:21:12.439 --> 00:21:13.906
You think you can?

487
00:21:13.940 --> 00:21:14.941
Okay.

488
00:21:18.845 --> 00:21:21.414
I'll just sleep on the floor.
all right?

489
00:21:21.448 --> 00:21:22.515
Don't be stupid.

490
00:21:41.133 --> 00:21:42.969
Look. Peyton...

491
00:21:43.002 --> 00:21:48.441
I just wish there was something
i could do or say

492
00:21:48.475 --> 00:21:51.344
to help you through this.

493
00:21:51.378 --> 00:21:53.546
You already have.

494
00:21:53.580 --> 00:21:55.382
Thanks. Lucas.

495
00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:02.422
[ Sighs deeply ]

496
00:22:04.991 --> 00:22:06.393
Good night.

497
00:22:06.426 --> 00:22:07.394
Good night.

498
00:22:19.105 --> 00:22:22.108
I'm sorry
you had to see that.

499
00:22:22.141 --> 00:22:23.476
It's okay.

500
00:22:23.510 --> 00:22:25.478
It helped me understand you.

501
00:22:29.916 --> 00:22:33.085
[ Sighs ]

502
00:22:33.119 --> 00:22:34.854
You know. growing up.

503
00:22:34.887 --> 00:22:38.758
there were certain things that
were just carved into stone.

504
00:22:38.791 --> 00:22:42.662
And the main one was that
Dan Scott would have been a pro

505
00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:44.764
if he didn't blow out
his knee.

506
00:22:44.797 --> 00:22:46.499
So. all this time.

507
00:22:46.533 --> 00:22:49.536
he's just been feeding me
this line of crap

508
00:22:49.569 --> 00:22:52.138
about how great
he would have been.

509
00:22:52.171 --> 00:22:55.374
And how I'd never be
as good as him.

510
00:22:58.177 --> 00:22:59.912
Bastard.

511
00:22:59.946 --> 00:23:03.483
At least you know
the truth. though. right?

512
00:23:03.516 --> 00:23:06.486
[ Scoffs ]

513
00:23:06.519 --> 00:23:09.689
I just don't know
what to do with it.

514
00:23:09.722 --> 00:23:11.023
Okay.

515
00:23:11.057 --> 00:23:12.525
Good night.

516
00:23:12.559 --> 00:23:13.693
Good night.

517
00:23:13.726 --> 00:23:15.194
I'm here
if you need me. okay?

518
00:23:15.227 --> 00:23:16.463
All right.

519
00:23:20.667 --> 00:23:25.638
Hey. remember how I said
my family's so screwed up.

520
00:23:25.672 --> 00:23:28.741
nothing new would make
a difference?

521
00:23:28.775 --> 00:23:30.443
Yeah.

522
00:23:30.477 --> 00:23:31.644
I was wrong.

523
00:23:45.725 --> 00:23:49.629
[ Footsteps ]

524
00:23:49.662 --> 00:23:51.664
You want to hear
my side of it?

525
00:23:51.698 --> 00:23:53.132
Why should I believe it?

526
00:23:53.165 --> 00:23:55.535
This whole time
you've been riding me.

527
00:23:55.568 --> 00:23:57.804
you've known exactly
the way I feel.

528
00:23:57.837 --> 00:23:59.238
Now that that's in my head.

529
00:23:59.271 --> 00:24:01.541
it just makes it
that much worse.

530
00:24:05.512 --> 00:24:09.081
I was a great player.
Nathan. in high school.

531
00:24:09.115 --> 00:24:11.183
But when I got to Carolina.

532
00:24:11.217 --> 00:24:14.086
I knew it wasn't gonna be
the same.

533
00:24:16.689 --> 00:24:18.691
My dad couldn't see it.
though.

534
00:24:18.725 --> 00:24:21.060
It was hard
on your grandmother. too.

535
00:24:21.093 --> 00:24:22.962
So. when I got hurt.

536
00:24:22.995 --> 00:24:27.534
she came to me and pleaded
with me to walk away.

537
00:24:27.567 --> 00:24:31.237
She said it would be better
for all of us.

538
00:24:31.270 --> 00:24:32.471
So I did.

539
00:24:35.007 --> 00:24:39.045
Worst decision of my life.

540
00:24:39.078 --> 00:24:42.549
It felt good to get out
from underneath my father.

541
00:24:42.582 --> 00:24:44.283
And then after a while.

542
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:47.587
I realized I wasn't playing
for him at all.

543
00:24:47.620 --> 00:24:49.756
The game meant the world
to me.

544
00:24:49.789 --> 00:24:53.760
I just never took the time
to stand back and realize that.

545
00:24:53.793 --> 00:24:56.796
So I tried
to get back into it.

546
00:24:56.829 --> 00:24:58.998
Rehab. running. weights.

547
00:24:59.031 --> 00:25:02.769
It was too late.
My knee never responded.

548
00:25:04.704 --> 00:25:07.206
It was over for me.

549
00:25:07.239 --> 00:25:09.609
So you think that
somehow gives you the right

550
00:25:09.642 --> 00:25:11.043
to hammer me all the time?

551
00:25:11.077 --> 00:25:13.546
I know I push you.
I know I'm hard on you.

552
00:25:13.580 --> 00:25:15.882
But I'm trying to save you
of a life of regret.

553
00:25:15.915 --> 00:25:17.550
Trust me.
you don't want it.

554
00:25:17.584 --> 00:25:20.286
So then. you make me feel
like crap all the time.

555
00:25:20.319 --> 00:25:21.788
It really helps. dad.

556
00:25:21.821 --> 00:25:23.222
I could have been stronger.

557
00:25:23.255 --> 00:25:25.592
But I push you
so you will be.

558
00:25:25.625 --> 00:25:28.695
so things will end up better
for you than they did for me.

559
00:25:28.728 --> 00:25:30.129
Then you're safe. dad.

560
00:25:30.162 --> 00:25:32.865
There's no way I'm ever
gonna end up like you.

561
00:25:53.686 --> 00:25:54.887
Hey.

562
00:25:54.921 --> 00:25:56.155
Hey.

563
00:25:56.188 --> 00:25:58.658
What you got?

564
00:25:58.691 --> 00:25:59.826
[ Sighs ]

565
00:25:59.859 --> 00:26:02.294
"To my heart. love. dad."

566
00:26:02.328 --> 00:26:06.065
He gave it to me
on my last birthday.

567
00:26:09.636 --> 00:26:11.270
What if it's him. Lucas?

568
00:26:11.303 --> 00:26:12.939
It's not gonna be.

569
00:26:12.972 --> 00:26:14.907
'Cause I don't know what --

570
00:26:14.941 --> 00:26:16.308
it's gonna be okay.

571
00:26:16.342 --> 00:26:20.112
I just keep trying to picture
walking into that room

572
00:26:20.146 --> 00:26:25.985
and seeing him lying there...
But I hit a wall.

573
00:26:26.018 --> 00:26:27.620
Why does it seem like

574
00:26:27.654 --> 00:26:30.723
every time things
are finally gonna be okay.

575
00:26:30.757 --> 00:26:32.725
something terrible happens?

576
00:26:32.759 --> 00:26:34.694
You don't know that it has.

577
00:26:42.368 --> 00:26:45.604
Keep him close
to your heart. Peyton.

578
00:26:48.174 --> 00:26:49.876
Get some sleep. okay?

579
00:27:10.296 --> 00:27:13.232
You can sleep in the bedroom.
I'll stay out here tonight.

580
00:27:17.770 --> 00:27:21.207
Has it ever once bothered
your conscious

581
00:27:21.240 --> 00:27:25.411
that our entire relationship
is based on your lie?

582
00:27:25.444 --> 00:27:28.380
When you were forced
to walk away

583
00:27:28.414 --> 00:27:31.383
because of your so-called
injury.

584
00:27:31.417 --> 00:27:33.085
I dropped out. too.

585
00:27:33.119 --> 00:27:34.854
We both dropped out
to raise Nathan.

586
00:27:34.887 --> 00:27:36.388
Don't rewrite history.

587
00:27:36.422 --> 00:27:39.425
Oh. so you're the only one
who can play that game?

588
00:27:39.458 --> 00:27:41.127
I thought I knew the man

589
00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:43.362
I was choosing to spend
my life with.

590
00:27:43.395 --> 00:27:45.064
The injury was real. Deb.

591
00:27:45.097 --> 00:27:48.968
And. yes. I decided not
to rehab it. at first.

592
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:52.839
By the time I changed my mind.
it was too late.

593
00:27:52.872 --> 00:27:56.876
I did it in service
of you and Nathan.

594
00:27:56.909 --> 00:28:01.047
Now. I know how you'd hold it
against me for not telling you.

595
00:28:01.080 --> 00:28:04.283
but did you ever think that
maybe I did it...

596
00:28:04.316 --> 00:28:06.385
To protect you
from it all?

597
00:28:09.255 --> 00:28:11.791
If that's what you need
to believe.

598
00:28:11.824 --> 00:28:12.959
It's the truth.

599
00:28:12.992 --> 00:28:18.297
The truth?
In this house?

600
00:28:42.088 --> 00:28:43.790
What's all this?

601
00:28:43.823 --> 00:28:47.426
Oh. sorry.
I didn't mean to wake you.

602
00:28:47.459 --> 00:28:49.095
I wasn't asleep.

603
00:28:49.128 --> 00:28:52.364
I hit the vending machines.
Hungry?

604
00:28:52.398 --> 00:28:55.902
You should probably eat
something.

605
00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:05.511
After my mom died. um.
my dad couldn't cook.

606
00:29:05.544 --> 00:29:10.449
so we lived on frozen pizzas
for the longest time.

607
00:29:10.482 --> 00:29:11.550
[ Chuckles ]

608
00:29:11.583 --> 00:29:13.352
I could live on pizza.

609
00:29:13.385 --> 00:29:16.823
He'd. um -- he'd buy
these cheese pizzas.

610
00:29:16.856 --> 00:29:20.026
and then he'd put
his own toppings on --

611
00:29:20.059 --> 00:29:23.195
pickles. bologna.
pineapple. whatever.

612
00:29:23.229 --> 00:29:24.363
That's nasty.

613
00:29:24.396 --> 00:29:27.333
No. actually.
they were really good.

614
00:29:27.366 --> 00:29:30.903
I think he did it mostly
just to make me laugh.

615
00:29:30.937 --> 00:29:34.306
You know. to help me forget
for a little bit.

616
00:29:34.340 --> 00:29:36.308
[ Alarm beeps ]

617
00:29:42.214 --> 00:29:43.983
[ Sighs ]

618
00:29:44.016 --> 00:29:45.885
You ready?

619
00:29:48.054 --> 00:29:49.889
No.

620
00:29:53.092 --> 00:29:55.161
Let's go.

621
00:30:11.543 --> 00:30:12.311
Morning.

622
00:30:12.344 --> 00:30:13.612
Morning.

623
00:30:13.645 --> 00:30:17.149
Scrambled or fried?
What do you think?

624
00:30:17.183 --> 00:30:20.186
I think nobody's gonna
be that hungry.

625
00:30:20.219 --> 00:30:24.090
I'm glad you stood up
to royal the way you did. Deb.

626
00:30:24.123 --> 00:30:26.092
I didn't mean to hurt Dan.

627
00:30:26.125 --> 00:30:30.062
but this lying over the years
has gotten so tiresome.

628
00:30:30.096 --> 00:30:33.599
I did what I thought I had to do
to save my son.

629
00:30:33.632 --> 00:30:36.168
That's what we do.

630
00:30:36.202 --> 00:30:39.005
I'm glad you spoke up.

631
00:30:41.640 --> 00:30:43.175
Dan?

632
00:30:43.209 --> 00:30:46.612
Son. you know. someday
you're gonna realize

633
00:30:46.645 --> 00:30:48.414
I did you a favor.

634
00:30:48.447 --> 00:30:52.084
Your daddy's gonna get
over this eventually.

635
00:30:52.118 --> 00:30:55.287
But if you let history
repeat itself.

636
00:30:55.321 --> 00:30:56.622
your son may not.

637
00:30:56.655 --> 00:30:58.557
I'm going for a run.

638
00:31:01.627 --> 00:31:05.364
Oh. well. I think I'll scramble
the eggs.

639
00:31:05.397 --> 00:31:06.432
Yeah.

640
00:31:11.070 --> 00:31:14.473
Listen. Nathan. uh...

641
00:31:14.506 --> 00:31:20.112
Whatever you're
going through. um...

642
00:31:20.146 --> 00:31:22.081
I'm sorry about your dad.

643
00:31:22.114 --> 00:31:24.984
I understand
why he did it. grandpa.

644
00:31:26.986 --> 00:31:29.688
He must have really loved you.
you know that?

645
00:31:29.721 --> 00:31:32.658
Because anything seemed better
than disappointing you.

646
00:31:59.685 --> 00:32:01.153
It's not him.

647
00:32:11.397 --> 00:32:12.664
You did good.

648
00:32:12.698 --> 00:32:16.002
I felt like my chest
was gonna explode.

649
00:32:23.375 --> 00:32:24.510
[ Cellphone rings ]

650
00:32:24.543 --> 00:32:25.277
Peyton's place?

651
00:32:25.311 --> 00:32:26.745
Hey. it's me.

652
00:32:26.778 --> 00:32:29.181
Hey. I was just dialing you.
That's freaky.

653
00:32:29.215 --> 00:32:31.050
Well. it's good news.

654
00:32:31.083 --> 00:32:33.152
Yeah. I know. I just got off
the phone with the coast guard.

655
00:32:33.185 --> 00:32:34.520
They made contact with his boat.
He's fine.

656
00:32:34.553 --> 00:32:35.654
[ Sighs ]

657
00:32:35.687 --> 00:32:37.990
They found your dad.
He's okay.

658
00:32:38.024 --> 00:32:39.158
Oh.

659
00:32:41.760 --> 00:32:43.595
All right.
We're headed home.

660
00:32:43.629 --> 00:32:44.730
Okay. I'm waiting.

661
00:32:44.763 --> 00:32:45.731
Love you.

662
00:32:45.764 --> 00:32:47.766
Love you. too. Bye.

663
00:32:47.799 --> 00:32:50.502
Oh. my god.
That's -- wait.

664
00:32:50.536 --> 00:32:51.537
What?

665
00:32:51.570 --> 00:32:52.704
Um. my bracelet.

666
00:32:52.738 --> 00:32:55.541
I must have left it
in the motel.

667
00:32:55.574 --> 00:32:57.609
All right. Let's go.

668
00:33:00.646 --> 00:33:01.713
Hey.

669
00:33:01.747 --> 00:33:03.582
Grandma's making breakfast.

670
00:33:03.615 --> 00:33:06.118
Show starts at 9:00.
You in?

671
00:33:06.152 --> 00:33:11.157
Um. as fun as last night was.
i think I'm gonna pass.

672
00:33:11.190 --> 00:33:14.660
You know. I've been thinking.

673
00:33:14.693 --> 00:33:17.663
Now that you know the truth
about your dad.

674
00:33:17.696 --> 00:33:19.298
you're free. right?

675
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:22.401
I mean. he's been lying to you
all this time.

676
00:33:22.434 --> 00:33:25.271
You don't have to listen to him
anymore.

677
00:33:25.304 --> 00:33:26.805
There's no more pressure.

678
00:33:26.838 --> 00:33:30.609
Yeah. I wish
that were true.

679
00:33:30.642 --> 00:33:32.344
What do you mean?

680
00:33:32.378 --> 00:33:34.413
[ Sighs ]

681
00:33:34.446 --> 00:33:36.615
My dad walked away.

682
00:33:36.648 --> 00:33:40.152
and his father will never
forgive him for that.

683
00:33:40.186 --> 00:33:41.553
I have to go back.

684
00:33:41.587 --> 00:33:42.588
Nathan --

685
00:33:42.621 --> 00:33:44.590
I have to beat him.
Haley.

686
00:33:44.623 --> 00:33:48.094
It's the only way I'm ever
gonna be free of my dad.

687
00:33:59.405 --> 00:34:01.240
It has to be in here.

688
00:34:08.314 --> 00:34:09.648
Got it?

689
00:34:12.751 --> 00:34:13.585
[ Crying ]

690
00:34:13.619 --> 00:34:14.753
Hey. it's okay.

691
00:34:14.786 --> 00:34:16.755
Everything's okay now.
okay?

692
00:35:44.276 --> 00:35:45.244
Ow. ow.

693
00:35:45.277 --> 00:35:46.445
Sorry. sorry.

694
00:35:46.478 --> 00:35:50.316
Hair --
it's in your necklace.

695
00:35:50.349 --> 00:35:51.917
Okay. okay.

696
00:35:51.950 --> 00:35:53.785
There.

697
00:35:53.819 --> 00:35:55.821
[ Laughs ]

698
00:35:57.723 --> 00:36:00.259
Brooke.

699
00:36:00.292 --> 00:36:01.493
What?

700
00:36:04.696 --> 00:36:07.165
Brooke gave me
that necklace.

701
00:36:12.604 --> 00:36:16.742
You know. we. um...

702
00:36:16.775 --> 00:36:19.745
We probably
should get going.

703
00:36:19.778 --> 00:36:20.712
Yeah.

704
00:36:22.281 --> 00:36:23.515
Okay.

705
00:36:28.254 --> 00:36:30.656
[ Breathes deeply ]

706
00:36:48.540 --> 00:36:51.277
How's business. Keith?

707
00:36:51.310 --> 00:36:53.512
It's pretty steady.

708
00:36:53.545 --> 00:36:54.513
Good.

709
00:36:56.548 --> 00:36:58.484
I know I rib you a lot. son.

710
00:36:58.517 --> 00:37:01.453
but I hope you know I think
you're a good man.

711
00:37:01.487 --> 00:37:02.754
That's great. dad.

712
00:37:02.788 --> 00:37:05.257
First nice thing
you say to me.

713
00:37:05.291 --> 00:37:07.526
and it's really
just a dig at Dan.

714
00:37:07.559 --> 00:37:10.362
Please. can we just eat
our breakfast?

715
00:37:16.468 --> 00:37:19.738
Dan. you forgot
to open your presents.

716
00:37:19.771 --> 00:37:22.808
This is from
your dad and me.

717
00:37:24.810 --> 00:37:26.378
Oh. okay.

718
00:37:39.625 --> 00:37:40.792
What's this?

719
00:37:40.826 --> 00:37:42.060
It's a quilt.

720
00:37:42.093 --> 00:37:44.430
A lady in Orlando made it.

721
00:37:44.463 --> 00:37:47.866
We still had all your old
basketball stuff.

722
00:37:47.899 --> 00:37:51.770
and I just couldn't bring
myself to throw 'em out.

723
00:37:51.803 --> 00:37:55.674
You see. son. you still have
a lot to be proud of.

724
00:38:07.619 --> 00:38:09.421
It's almost over. Deb.

725
00:38:09.455 --> 00:38:10.822
Thank god for that.

726
00:38:14.393 --> 00:38:15.661
[ Sighs ]

727
00:38:15.694 --> 00:38:18.497
Look. after all
that's happened.

728
00:38:18.530 --> 00:38:22.601
I want to thank you for not
throwing gas on the fire.

729
00:38:22.634 --> 00:38:24.970
You okay?

730
00:38:25.003 --> 00:38:27.539
No. no. Dan. I'm not.

731
00:38:27.573 --> 00:38:30.376
And we're not.

732
00:38:30.409 --> 00:38:32.411
All this pretending
and lying.

733
00:38:32.444 --> 00:38:34.846
I can't really hold it
against you.

734
00:38:34.880 --> 00:38:39.385
Because I realized
all these years...

735
00:38:39.418 --> 00:38:41.387
I've been doing it. too.

736
00:39:01.607 --> 00:39:02.674
Look. Peyton --

737
00:39:02.708 --> 00:39:03.675
don't.

738
00:39:05.477 --> 00:39:09.548
It was stupid. okay?
You're with Brooke now.

739
00:39:09.581 --> 00:39:11.783
Yeah.

740
00:39:11.817 --> 00:39:14.653
We just --
we got carried away.

741
00:39:14.686 --> 00:39:17.589
It didn't mean anything.

742
00:39:17.623 --> 00:39:19.891
It didn't?

743
00:39:21.960 --> 00:39:24.062
Of course it did.

744
00:39:32.838 --> 00:39:34.039
Bye. sweetie.

745
00:40:00.499 --> 00:40:02.100
See you later.
